%U A116195 2049430589972661489,2995303155542192885,4026214090447622723
%N A116195 Numbers k such that k concatenated with k+5 gives the product of two numbers which differ by 7.
%C A116195 If k+5 has d digits, the concatenation is k//k+5 = 10^d*k+k+5 = m*(m+7), therefore k//k-3 = 10^d*k+k-3 = (m-1)*(m+8), so there is a large overlap with A116140. - _R. J. Mathar_, May 22 2026
%e A116195 7717533//7717538 = 8784946 * 8784953, where // denotes concatenation.
%Y A116195 Cf. A116133, A116194, A116196, A116147, A116326.
